DOCUMENT();

loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'parserRadioButtons.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

Context('Numeric');

$radio = RadioButtons(
    [ [
        'Mode of travel to university (bus, car, bike or walk)',
        'Grade Point Average (GPA)',
        'Number of Economics courses',
        'Age (in years)',
        'Number of hours of study per week'
    ] ],
    0
);

BEGIN_PGML
Below is a list of variables from an annual survey of university students. Variables may be classified as either numerical or categorical. Which variable is categorical?

[_]{$radio}
END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The answer is mode of travel to university (bus, car, bike or walk).
END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
